

** How to organize "edit test"?  An example session...

Tue, 03 Nov 2009 08:54:33 -0800


qzm$ ls
 id    dsc        num_qs  total_time  score  time
 --    -----      ------  ----------  -----  ----
 FINISHED (readonly)
 1     csci10     10      00:30:00    80%    200%
 2     csci10.02  10      00:30:00    85%    150%
 UNFINISHED
 3     csci10.03  10      00:30:00    --	 --

qzm$ create csci10.04

qzm$ padd <test id> tag[s]=[csci10, factorial, integration] limit=10

qzm$ ls <test id>
qzm$ ls 3
 total questions: 10
 date: 2009-10-12
 tag            num_qs  % of total
 -----------    ------  ----------
 csci10         10      100
 factorial      5       50
 integration    5       50

qzm$ copy <src test id> <dest test id>
qzm$ lsq 3
  num   id
  ---   ---
  1.    132
  2.    101
  3.    10

qzm$ swapq 3 1
qzm$ lsq 3
  num   id
  ---   ---
  1.    10
  2.    101
  3.    132

qzm$ rmq 2
qzm$ lsq 3
  num   id
  ---   ---
  1.    10
  2.    132

qzm$ finish <test id>


** Problems stored as files?

Sun, 01 Nov 2009 12:55:58 -0800

It may be better to store each question as a file instead of stored
as a text string in a table.

* Simplifies editing.
* Version control of files.
* No escaping problems when importing/exporting data.

In the event that the database crashes the problems would not be lost.
